      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for that. the distinction between individualism and community is interesting. so when people talk about the \"natural\" progression of these societies, do most scholars agree that moving toward these complex, hierarchical modern structures is basically an inevitable step in human evolution? like, do primitive societies just naturally \"develop\" into civilizations over time?",
